{"can_edit": true, "from": {"name": "Micha\u00ebl Caron Couturier", "id": "1646843124"}, "revision": "10151922885470019", "updated_time": "2012-07-03T07:56:29+0000", "can_delete": true, "created_time": "2012-07-03T07:56:29+0000", "message": "<p>I find Linux more suited in  the long term, Os and apps updated as I want, I make the desktop that I  want, could choose my apps to run easily even on an older pc, old  hardware will be supported for a lifetime if included in the kernel or  with the windows driver for wifi on ndiswrapper, old games will always  work on Wine, I could go to 100% free softwares and evade all the  troubles coming from Adobe flash player, keep your files under your  control for a lifetime in an open format and open source hardware driver  keep my hardware usable for 20 years almost with a driverless pc so all  is plug and play, you could use a premodded kernel like realtime or  liquorix, performance always increase even with older hardware,  softwares are designed for users so it&#039;s quite pro-efficient for example  just plug an usb gamepad open Mplayer to watch a video, it will be  usable as a remote, the software are mostly open source so you could  participate to make them better and fork them if needed, they&#039;re usable  on any operating system even on a usb key while traveling, I could even  bring my OS on a usb and the apps repositories on an external harddrive,  I could install it to anyone like they want, security, for gaming I  even played Dirt 3 on a crap pc so it could handle any apps/games or  almost *check our documents*, I could keep my setings for years without  reinstalling while staying up-to-date, I could build it as I want and  make anything from it, you could multiboot or virtualize another  operating system if needed, you don&#039;t need Windows, you have Wine and  almost better apps alternatives ...</p>", "subject": "Some reasons to love Linux ;)", "id": "10151922885475019", "icon": "https://fbstatic-a.akamaihd.net/rsrc.php/v2/yi/r/-64q65AWgXb.png"}